{"type":"message","id":"ed787ed9","parentId":"031a0a17","timestamp":"2026-04-14T23:24:51.018Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me compare the actual changes vs the last report sent (which was at 22:55 UTC):\n\n**Changes since 22:55 UTC report:**\n1. `cron:53c5832a` (Daily Briefing) spawned at 23:16 UTC — NEW, not seen before\n2. `cron:e7885813-0446` (Agent Status to Lead) ran and completed normally at 23:14 UTC\n3. All other sessions stable\n\nThe key change: Daily Briefing cron ran at 23:16 UTC. This is notable - it's the scheduled daily briefing for 5AM UTC+7 (which is actually 22:00 UTC the previous day... wait that doesn't make sense).\n\n\nActually, looking at the label \"Daily Briefing 5AM UTC+7\" — at 23:16 UTC, that's 06:16 UTC+7, which is 1 hour 16 minutes after 5AM. So the briefing ran a bit late, but it did complete and sent the daily report successfully. Comparing the baseline from 23:11 UTC to now at 23:24 UTC, the QLHV monitor is still running, but there's a new Agent Status session that wasn't in the baseline, and the DTLX 5p Monitor is still cycling normally.\n\nThe daily briefing cron that appeared at 23:16 UTC was a one-time task that has now completed — it was triggered by the previous heartbeat session. Since the last report was at 22:55 UTC and the baseline is from 23:11 UTC, the daily briefing session is actually new activity that wasn't in the baseline. However, the last status report went out at 22:55 UTC, so I need to compare the current state at 23:24 UTC against that baseline to see what actually changed in the monitoring system.\n\nThe key differences are the daily briefing session completing around 23:16 UTC and the Agent Status session ending normally, but since both of these ran as scheduled tasks with expected outcomes, there's nothing meaningful to report — I'll stay quiet and just update the heartbeat state.","thinkingSignature":"73b7ea3c4114239ad9001bce1e5aafc3de6d11a68a24b95c3174d701d3829bfd"},{"type":"text","text":"Baseline vs current — all changes are expected lifecycle events (Daily Briefing ran as scheduled, Agent Status completed normally, cron cycling is normal). No new failures, no blockers. **Silent — no report.**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":153,"output":471,"cacheRead":14264,"cacheWrite":22728,"totalTokens":37616,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776209081152,"responseId":"062dffbab059d752421c24d464a1e5b1"}}
